caption: Other than the hair follicle at the bottom of my 🥣 The food was absolutely Delicious and Worth every penny 😋.
This place is fabulous! Isaiah our server was great!
The 12oz ribeye was great. Watching the chefs was great

So i come in for a carry out and the hostess decides to tell me the first ticket had a 12 minute time and there were 10 orders infront of me that i had to just wait. I wouldnt of thought of it as a big deal but i waited 30 minutes and customers that walked in to be seated were served their food first. Really did not care for the customer service and there excuse of being short staffed on a weekend. Food quality great so i give it 3 stars you can really ruin a person experience with poor customer service and ignoring the customers. Plus why would any kitchen put a cheesecake under a heated lamp next to hot food.
Good food, good beer, reasonable prices.
Stay away, very far away. Attitude at every turn

They Advertise a full Gluten Free menu, but when I asked for a gluten free menu the bartender didn’t know what I was talking about.  When I asked if a gluten free bun for my burger was an option I didn’t get a very hospitable answer.  I then asked about sides and what the vegetables of the day was, he said... “I think spinach,” but later I was brought broccoli...  just not very customer focused!  We had to ask for refills, and we were never asked if we wanted another beer.  Obviously not a high pressure bartender!  Food was good, but I’ll take my money elsewhere in the future!

GB's Brewery & Restaurant located at corner of Fourth Street Live in Louisville, Kentucky was a stop worth making.  The restaurant offered  enjoyable seating areas both inside and out.  Many surprise dishes on the menu.  My server Chloe, recommended the Shrimp & Lobster Macaroni & Cheese.  It did not disappoint, incredibly tasty and loaded with seafood.  Try their Microbrewed beers and take home a few growlers or two. Tell them that Terrance Ray of Sunshine sent you.

Awful service.  Sat there for over 15 minutes before they even took our drink order. Took for ever to get food. Had to send it back because it wasn't cooked properly. waited for over 20 minutes for redo on the food but never got it. Had to cancel order and walk out. Extremely disappointed. Do not recommend.  EDIT: I filled out the contact form as requested.  EDIT #2 (3/16/2021): It has been over a week and no one has ever contacted me back after I filled out the form.

We were in town for daughters cheer events, it was also my birthday. I was happy to get back to GB, since we don’t have a location in Indiana.  The Marzen is good as it has always been !! I was disappointed that they have removed most of traditional German items from menu, not even a pork chop (reason for 4 stars)!  Food is very good, staff are very helpful and attentive.
Our server Garrett was really nice! Our food on the other hand was less than good 3/4 of our meals were completely inedible 🥺 our wait time was entirely unacceptable for the quality of food.
Fantastic service, and fantastic food and super affordable prices.
Im real, mad I got the macaroni and lobster only -one Lobster it was not worth $20 if i can give a -0 i would

I feel really bad for the staff here. They are clearly overwhelmed and understaffed. They are working hard but not able to get the job done in a decent amount of time. Plan on 10 minutes becoming 20 and 30 minutes becoming an hour. After previous good experiences here we had a recent stretch of difficult service.
Every time I’ve eaten here it’s been fantastic. And the staff is friendly, highly recommend

Friendly staff, great beer and awesome food. It's impressive that they make their own house beer on location and use a lot of fresh ingredients in the kitchen. Also, they have a really inviting dining room/patio. It's a shame that covid has changed the way restaurants operate at the moment but once things go back to normal I'll most likely stop by to have a nice pie by the fire pit.
Great place
6 servers, 8 tables, no service. We went somewhere else! Maybe the food is good? Idk. Good luck!
Fabulous! as always.
Great spot for lunch or dinner! The steak was cooked right, the broccoli tasted great, and the waitress was kind!
What an incredible micro-brewery!! Wonderful food, fantastic staff, and a good place to "chill". Highly recommend this eatery located in the heart of Louisville, KY.

Stopped in for a quick bite and stayed for hours!! Had the best service, Veronika was sweet and knows her customer service, gave me great suggestions since I'm just visiting and had never seen this menu before. Outside seating by the fire pit was lovely. Before leaving town we'll be sure to stop in again, but only if Veronika is working!!

This place used to be great. One of my favorite restaurants in the downtown area. Yesterday's visit was not what I expected. My wife ordered boneless wings and was brought regular wings. When we mentioned it to our waitress she said that they no longer have boneless wings. Why didn't she tell us that when we ordered? I ordered the fish tacos which used to be incredible but they changed them. They are now different and saying that they were "ok" is being generous. The beer is still great so that's why I gave it 3 stars.
Best stop yet on our 3 day trip from Ohio
We had the chop salad and it was just about perfect. Service is friendly. Pretty day outside.
Food was incredible and the server and manager were amazing glad we stopped here for dinner.
Good food food, friendly service.

If you are just going to drink beer I assume this is a good spot. 1.) DRINKS: I tried two different mixed drinks that were really bad.  A peach whiskey drink with jack Daniels that was light on the whiskey. and mango mojito that tasted like dirty old sprite. It was way too much seltzer or something.  I was also hungry so I was not that interested in the drink but I usually like to enjoy a mojito with dinner.  2) APPETIZERS/FOOD: The food was not good either.! It was pretty bad. I sent back the artichoke crab dip because the cheese tasted like hot thousand island dressing and the crostinis were either old or cooked with too much oil or something. This is my first trip to this location.  I’ve had food at the restaurant in Waikiki/Honolulu area that was amazing (I also wrote a review about that location). The Cajun wings were a little over cooked and just not great flavor. The shrimp and lobster tacos were really bland.  Only two of the three tacos had shrimp.  3.) SERVICE: The service was ok. I was waited on at the bar by a young lady named Savannah who was nice.  She was friendly and kept checking on me and didn’t have any problem when I needed to send back the appetizer. The bar back Or other server was a guy who assisted but I couldn’t tell if he was supposed to be there because initially when I sat down he was just there talking to her about schedules or the weekend for about ten minutes while she went back and forth serving. I didn’t get his name because he never introduced himself or even asked if I needed anything until I was done with my food and he wanted to get my plates out of the way.  Presumably so I could leave faster.  He was eager to help the other people that came to the bar not sure if it was because I was the only black person at the bar or they just had a system set up while it was busy that he would help everyone except one or two people.  But it did seem like he was ignoring me while he washed dishes right in front of me and practically splashing dish water in my food. The other female bartender was just making the servers drinks which is understandable but she did at least acknowledge me and have someone get me a menu when I sat down. I’ve been a server /bartender for years before my current job so I know how busy Saturday nights can get.  you can not have people at the bar that are not very friendly or give the appearance of being discriminatory towards a certain group. That is unacceptable service. He also seemed to ignore the other black man that sat on the opposite side of the bar but that was just my experience. Im sure that is not the standard. Overall it was not a great experience and I would not come back to this location unless I was with a group that just wanted drinks or something. The downtown area is a nice place to go with a group for a night out.
Excellent.
Wildly understaffed. Bartender was overwhelmed and very rude.
bar food and the atmosphere here is excellent. The service here is above par.
A bit greasy. Not many vegetarian options
Food was at an Applebee’s level except for Bavarian pretzel.

Really recomendable place, I can tell for sure that they have the best beer in town. I have tried all their beers and I can say that Marzen lager beer is one of the best they have, we visit this place frecuently, prices are good and food is also good.
Had fish and chips with the garlic chips.....AMAZING!!
The food here was excellent. They have a really good draft beer selection. The customer service was also really good.
Great salmon!
Over priced and food is average. Beer isnt rated great and doesnt taste great. Wont be back.
Over priced and the beer is average at best. Same sentiments about the food.
Great drafts and delicious food for a reasonable price.  Definitely going back!

Came in with a large group (15+) on a tight schedule in between meetings. The waiters were attentive and helpful in letting our group know what options were faster for the kitchen staff to prepare. The chicken and mushroom pasta was the perfect portion for lunch - although a bit pricy at ~$15 for this bowl.. a friend had the shrimp and mango tacos (a filling 3 tacos and black beans). Minus one star just for a little confusion during the handing out/collection of checks. Otherwise a great experience! The appetizers looked delicious, and their drink menu looked excellent. Definitely coming back when we have more time to enjoy our food!
Excellent food and beer
Very good food and service!
They don't answer the phone to make a reservation.  Plenty of other options

We saw the Jim Beam sign above the restaurant from our hotel and we thought it was a new restaurant. It was actually G&B.  Terence was our waiter and he was amazing and knowledgeable.  We both got Salads.  I got the chopped salad and my wife got the Shrimp Cobb.  But she requested the Shrimp be replaced with grilled chicken.  Terence didn’t even have to ask the kitchen. He bragged that everything was made from scratch and so that wouldn’t be a problem.  The food was great. They had so many beers to choose from. My wife decided to get a flight and let Terence pick for her.  The menu says 5 for 5, but they brought out 6. She loved all but one which was a little too hoppy for her liking.  The darkest beer was very smooth.

This is a chain, so nothing especially unique here. I was not feeling well when I was here for dinner, but the small Caesar salad and side bowl of rice were healthy, inexpensive, and not too filling. Otherwise the menu is full of large portions and not-too-healthy items. I was here with a party of approximately 30 people and the staff was very accommodating of our needs. Nice work!

This place was alright, which I guess is expected from a chain. The food we got was good, the service was alright, and the drinks were good. There was a server that always returned to his computer station and would yell curse words and “JESUS my shoulder hurts!” with no one around... kind of bizarre.
Very heavy food, not great for lunch.

Original waiter looked at us and said before greeting, "What a waste..." to another waiter and we were subsequently not greeted for over 15 minutes.  Atmosphere was 4/5 Beer was 4/5 stars Appetizer fries was 2/5 Both our $15 meals were 3/5  Overall, we very disappointed, mostly because of the initial service, especially after driving 3 hours to here.
Great food, good staff. Recommend visiting.
i thought this was a nice place to eat. Good atmosphere and the food wasn't bad. I had 3 fish tacos. My boyfriend enjoyed it more. So that makes for a 5-star review!
This place was good. Amazing services. Great atmosphere. Everything was well maintained. I went there with my friend for lunch. Sitting section was comfortable and beautiful.
Nice waiter, okay food. The patio and chairs were pretty dirty (bird poop). "Neapolitan crust" flatbreads come on a dry, crunchy cracker crust. Tacos were good.
Full gluten free menu and great service! I had the bruschetta chicken which came with amazing zoodles, they made it dairy free for me as well and I didn’t get sick! What a great option!

While I prefer locally owned restaurants, I've never had a bad meal at this franchise.  The food isn't authentic German, but the menu has some German dishes.  My favorite is the chicken schnitzel!  I love the lemon and the capers on that dish.  If you enjoy beer, then you need to check out their selection. My friend got a flight of 6 beers for only $5.
The "Golden export" is worth the visit. Excellent beer.
Pretty cool bar. Nice staff!
Great food but table service was slow.
We come here often.Their Hefeweizen is off the chart.
Nice place downtown. Decent food on the menu.

Came in tonight with my brother, we were promptly seated, waited for 15 mins to be served, had at least 3 servers walk past, one of which I caught her eye as I raised me hand and she nodded at me, but proceeded to go about her job. We walked out they won't be receiving our business again! Very poor form!

We went to this place on Saturday Memorial weekend. Place was not crowded so we asked for outdoor seating. Took awhile for the server to get to our table he seamed lost and confused not sure why. It took forever to get our drink order and when we did get the food it was just dropped off he never came by and asked if we needed anything. We had to ask the host for our check or we would still be there. I gave this 2 stars because the food was not bad but the service was terrible.
Great food. Great beer.  Carl was our server. Give that man a raise. He was excellent.
Nachos were great, beer flight was alright. I would come back for the food only.

Visited this establishment multiple times during St. Patty's Day weekend. We were in town for a cheer event. We were able to walk in and be seated, even with large groups. The fries were amazing. As was the rest of my food. Wait staff was very accommodating, especially when in a time crunch. My picky-eating teenager had zero complaints. Food and drinks were great and the service was awesome. We will definitely return. One of the few places that was prepared and able to accommodate the crowds of that weekend.

I just experienced the BEST stout I’ve ever had! The menu looked amazing and the food I did have did NOT disappoint. The service was beyond excellent and everyone was wicked friendly! Maggie even gave an amazingly educational tour of the brewery with such passion I may just switch careers! 😉 Super impressed! Highly recommend!

I’m giving this 2 stars due to the food but that’s about it. The service was absolutely horrid. The server never came by after food was delivered to check on us. The first set of drinks took 15 minutes and it took about 10 minutes to even come over and say hi. The food was decent nothing to write home about but the thing that kinda upset me was the fact that the sirloin I got was supposed to have the mushroom sauce on the side... it was not and I couldn’t complain because no one came by until we were ready to leave. I probably won’t be back due to the service and the issue with the food. Our server didn’t initiate any conversation at all with us and we were on a date.
Everything is pricey, but everything is delicious. Make sure to get a flight of their beers!
Was really good.

Food and table service were good.  Host took our name and said 45 minutes.  He forgot about us and it turned into over an hour and a half.   Didn't care for seeing staff reach in to items on prep area and eat them where food was being prepared.  Will not go here again.
The food and the service was great!
Austin our server,  is Outstanding!  Food was great! Keep up the good work!

We had an AMAZING time here! Wound up at GB on accident and was so glad we did. Tasty reasonably-priced food (had the Chicken and Mushroom Pasta), really fast service, friendly employees, and wonderful atmosphere! While there are other nationally known chain restaurants close by, this is a local spot we will remember from our time in Louisville. Loved it, highly recommend!  Also, try the Hefeweizen. It is best I've had and I'm from a very German-beer loving city (Cincinnati, OH).
(Translated by Google) Friendly employees. Tasty homemade beer and snacks. It is a favorite restaurant.  (Original) 친절한 종업원. 맛잇는 수제 맥주와 안주. 정말 마음에 드는 식당이다.
Great service!
Went there to watch a basketball game during lunch. Had a good experience there overall. Food, service, and atmosphere were all good.
Great pub burger and wonderful local brews! Awesome service for such a busy night. Thank you Brooke for keeping up with everyone!
Food was delicious! Waiters were not attentive.

The beer is brewed perfectly. The food is great and the bartenders are friendly. There are plenty of TV's and they should have the game on you want. If not, just ask. Fourth Street live has a few options but definitely give GB a shot.
Delicious food and great in house crafted beer

Walked in and got seated immediately. There was hardly anybody else in the restaurant at the time. Asked for a high chair which never showed up. Waited 15 minutes and nobody came over to serve us. After multiple servers kept walking by us we packed up and left.
Amazing!

The food was good. My meal was great. Our server, Victoria, was very responsive to our requests. The only negative was a couple of menu items were sold out which was surprising for a Wednesday evening. Otherwise, the venue was sufficient as the prelude to our Black Violin performance at the Brown Theater.
Place was amazing loved the glass window kitchen,Food was great presentation and taste.Beer is absolutely refreshing.
Food was good & prices but service a bit on the slow. Had to ask for flatware.
Food awesome...beer, eh

We waited as they tried to figure out how to honor a reservation they had lost for a party of 7, including 2 six olds. We had the email confirmation and waited 30 minutes for the best answer to be to continue to wait. Yes, I am using wait repeatedly. Eventually (and forevermore), we took our business down the street. There are locals who come to your restaurant, perhaps service should be slightly more of an emphasis.

Perfect! That counts for pretty much everything. The various beer have a very good taste all on their own and the food is amazing. It's so fresh and just perfectly seasoned! Plus we got a nice table where we were able to look into the kitchen. Our waiter was a bit quick when talking, other than that very helpful and kind.
Wonderful meal! Veronica was our great server. Couldn't ask for a better steak.

They have a Gluten Free / Gluten Sensitive menu.  The server and I talked extensively about ordering from that menu.  Unfortunately, my burger ended up with a regular bun but I didn't know until it was too late.  Dangerous for Celiacs.
THEY DO NOT ANSWER THEIR PHONE.
Food was good and service was great.
It was our first time there!! Food was great server was very friendly and fast service as well. Will definitely be back
Great beer selection.  Food and service were also great. Probably one of the most reasonably priced places on 4th Street Live.

The first 3 appetizers we picked were all sold out, took over 20mins for them to tell us.  Ordered an old fashioned, made by someone who doesn’t know how to make them or was their first time.  Service was okay, seemed he had too many tables or other things going on.  Location and ambiance was on point.  Food was okay. Who ever made the Calamari needs to be retrained on how to make it properly. Breading was falling off and squid was rubber; cooked too long.  I ordered the pasta mushroom and smoked chicken. Barry any chicken but good taste.

This place was HORRIBLE! The service was rude and the cooks got 2 of our orders wrong and when one was brought out fixed...it was STILL WRONG!!! The food was not worth the amount of money you have to pay for it.  My friends and I were excited to try something new and were ALL so let down! All 5 of us are in total agreement we will not come back and absolutely will not be recommending this to anyone!
Great burgers, cold local beer!!
Wait staff is fantastic and the food is out of this world.
Friends took us to this place couple years ago, since that we like to drop by here time to times. Marzen is perfect for those who like malty beer.
atmosphere was welcoming
Needed to get in contact with an employee, called the restaurant, phone was answered (after 10 rings each time) and immediately hung up on for 5 consecutive calls.  Very poor customer service.
This was a very nice spot.  The service was friendly and fast.  The food was hot and very fresh.  I enjoyed myself this afternoon.  I will be back and bring my family.
The watress was wonderful and the food and beer we're great!!
I'm definitely a fan of the kolby beef burger!!!
Excellent meal. The Gorgonzola Pear Salad was one of the best salads I have ever tasted.
Waiter was pleasant.  Food was not bad, and atmosphere was welcoming.  Will have to visit again during a busier time to give a more detailed review.
The beer was good. Food fair

We stumbled across this restaurant during our stay in Louisville as this one closes a bit later than other restaurants during the weekday. I really like their Marzen BBQ burger. I ended swapping a regular patty for the kobe patty and I thought it was pretty amazing. Since they are also their own brewery, I'd try their German beer! I personally ordered a Scharzbier and a Marzen and I liked both of them! Speaking of, I forgot to mention, I really like their fish and chips. Since coming back from London, I had not had any good fish and chips until I came into GB. Most places I've been to since returning to the US, put too much batter into the fish.
Party of 10.  Brooke was amazing.  Food was perfection.   I come here every year when I'm in town for a conference.
Wonderful service. Staff friendly and quick seating.
Reasonable food and service but below average beer, you’ll do better elsewhere but okay in a bind
Great pretzels with cheese dip.  Good beer.  Nice outdoor area
Good service and atmosphere.  We just ordered appetizers, not too bad but only rates 3 stars.  It's worth a visit though.
Stop #309 for @pizzas365: Gordon Biersch Brewery Restaurant has a perfectly fine, albeit greasy, pizza. It's not very unique, but the price is okay. 3.6 Stars.
They hosted our private party for 70 people. Great food. Great staff. No one with me had anything negative to say.

Decent beers made onsite. Not weird with fruit or other strange additives and true to their traditional styles. I had the chicken schnitzel and spaezle which was authentic and good with the Altbier. Wait staff was attentive, efficient and friendly without intruding.
The Cajun pasta is the way to go!
Great atmosphere and outstanding food.

We went in on a Saturday afternoon about 4:30pm. The restaurant was not even half filled at the time as it was relatively early.  The inside and the outside of the restaurant had a nice look and we had high hopes for a good experience. After being seated relatively quickly and provided menus, a waiter/waitress never came by to take a drink or food order. My wife and I waited for at least 10-15 minutes. We ended up leaving and going elsewhere.  A disappointing experience.
Tasty beer and food, with great service.

I visited this location two times on a recent business trip to Louisville. The first night I went I was on my own and got a Kobe burger, one of their craft beers and some of their wings. I really enjoyed the food, and the beer. The waitress, and trainee, did a great job and made it easy for the return visit. This time I came with 3 co-workers. I pretty much ordered the same thing, but this time what a difference. Our waitress was not very attentive to us. We had to ask other staff for refills. As we ordered the wings she did not bother to ask if we wanted bone in or boneless. Our mistake as we should have specified as we got boneless. They tasted good but not what we really wanted. The presentation of the food was like they just put it on the plate and brought it out. It was a night and day difference from my first visit. This is why the lower ranking as the food was still great, but the service the second time left no one impressed. To be  honest we talked less about our meal and more on how bad out experience was. There was only 2 of us from out of town and the 2 locals were even surprised about the visit.
Good beer, good food, service was slightly inattentive
Awesome restaurant with variety choice of craft beers and food. 5 star
Great service, great beers and amazing food!

Prime time location. Visited from out of town and great place to catch a game. I know this is a chain bit they were very accommodating, changing channels to show all the games and great wait staff. Faith is the best!!
Good food good service
Great spot, beers where very good and food was decent! For the price I'd go back.
It took forever to get our food.
Food was great!  Drinks were good.  Waiter could have had some more knowledge on the beers served but otherwise good experience
Great food and reasonably priced drinks. Both samon and steak were perfect.
Fantastic food! Great service too!
Good food. Great fast service.
Always a good meal
Very good food along with great service
Love the garlic fries.  Staff is helpful and attentive.

Was not happy with my meal, Had it delivered by doordash, and 1/3 of order was not delivered.  The manager he said he would make it right,  and deliverd it himself. And he did, wow. Now that is taking customer service to the next level. And the food was great. Thank you for making my special night, special. And the garlic fries are to die for.
Great place to eat. Veronicka was great!
Eh...

Ate twice here during my stay.  Had an amazing friendly waiter the first time and  a sweet lady the next night.  Food was amazing, good portions for price. Bartender made good drinks. Everything came out in a timely manner, hot and exactly how we ordered.  Will definitely come back and have recommended this spot for anyone going to be in the area.
Love the beer
Great atmosphere and very friendly waitstaff. I was very impressed with the portion size and tastes of the food. We went during happy hour and got $3 off alcoholic beverages.
Excellent brews and food. We had the brat sliders and the 10 ounce sirloin steak. Very good.
Outstanding service and craft beers..
Great microbrewery with good food and good atmosphere!
Nice food and beer
Food was good
Enjoyed sitting on the patio sipping drinks and enjoying the apple desserts.

I was in a group of four around 6:00 on a Friday night. There were multiple empty tables around us. We waited about 20 minutes after being seated for anyone to take our drink order. We then waited about 30 minutes to get our drinks and order our food. After ordering, we waited an hour to get our food. We were seated by the kitchen window and saw portions of our food sit under the heat lamps for at least 45 minutes. Our server didn’t know beers at all and had no clue as to which beer was actually on tap. Their electronic beer menu was out of date. Out of the four beers we attempted to order from said menu were not on tap. When we got our food my pizza, one of the 45 minute heat lamp items, was limp and rubbery. One girl sent her sausages back because she watched them sit for so long. The manager happened to be serving her the food and when she brought it out was short and didn’t give an apology. Our server was slow and spent most of her time at the computer talking to other servers. It was a horrible experience.
Wonderful time with great food and are waitress Stephanie was so awesome. She knew everything about the food and restaurant. Will be going back again. You can also eat in or out side the restaurant.
Overpriced, over-salted portions. The steak was meh, the spatzle meh, the vegetables meh+. Wouldn't recommend it to anyone.
The best
Varied menu, reasonably priced, nice atmosphere, excellent service!
Great place. Quite the menu. And the chef, Andy Chaney, rocked!
Great craft beer, good food, and fantastic service.  Highly recommended!
Great food at affordable price. Very friendly and helpful staff.

Good food, good service.  We were there late on Sat, no college so quiet.  Bartender was awesome, food was a little slow so she covered our drink.  Large beers, good price.  Had California burger and garlic fries and fresh made nachos.
Ribeye was fatty but shrimp and lobster mac and cheese was very good.

The food was great.  We had a fabulous waiter, Paul.  Great experience.  The weather was amazing, so we were able to sit outside.  The drinks were delicious as well.  Good atmosphere.  Definitely worth a trip

Just got here. Menu didn't show prices, waiter didn't know the prices, didn't offer to find them out. One price that was on the menu was that beers were 3 dollars on Tuesday. I tried to order a 3 dollar beer, per the menu, the waiter informed me that that deal no longer exists.  Not a great first impression, hope our drinks are good!  Update: My flight of beers came out, it's a flight of 6, instead of 5 like was on the menu. Came with a sheet that shows the beers, so clearly this is intentional. Hopefully I get charged properly!  Update 2: My wife ordered a tea half an hour ago and reminded the waiter once. Still no sign of it, but he has tried to sell us more. Interesting, since we haven't gotten what we ordered initially.  Final update: The drink that never showed up was comped, and brought out in a to-go cup. Still was the wrong drink, but a step in the right direction. He then brought out the correct drink. He also comped a soda my friend had gotten. My flight was charged properly.  It seemed the waiter was busy, and perhaps flustered. If this is the case, on a Tuesday night, perhaps Gordon Biersch needs to hire more staff.  All in all, my purchase was fine, but the service was pretty bad. I'll bump it up to 2 stars for the comp, but overall a pretty terrible experience from the start.
Lots of choices on the menu.  Food was good.  Liked the beer choices.
You get to test taste to bourbon
Great food and quick service!

A very cute and busy restaurant on 4th Street. Definitely make a reservation if at all possible, and for your convenience, their website hosts the online reservation tool, Opentable, that makes it hassle free. The service seemed a little chaotic and a couple things did go wrong with our order and the timing of our food was all over the place.  On the plus side though, the food and drinks were delicious, and there are more items on the menu I'd like to try. I'll definitely be back, perhaps not during the dinner rush, but I do recommend eating there.
Great food and beer. Awesome location to sit outside and eat.
Food was expected elleng, especially our burgers.  Their fries are just about the best ever
So sloooooooooow. Not good

Myself and some co-workers ate at Gordon Biersch tonight. I don't consider myself a "foodie" by any means. In fact, I sometimes get 'diners remorse' when the food doesn't stack up to the hefty price of the meal. Having said that, my dining experience at the Gordon Biersch Brewery was quite a memorable experience. I had a steak which had it not been for witnesses, would have warranted me licking the plate clean. Supurb food, fantastic service, and a classy atmosphere.

We come here when we're in Louisville at least once.  You can have about any local craft beer or mixed drink.  The wines are very good if selection is limited. But the big draw is everyone can find food they will want to eat.  And, it's always go at a reasonable price.

Great restaurant right at 4th Street live. We had the grilled salmon and BBQ burger. Food is delicious, sides were amazing, large selection of beers. I would definitely recommend this restaurant. It was busy on a Saturday night so the table service was a little long, but it was to be expected. The hefeweizen beer is a must try.
Great location. Beer and food is pretty average at best. We had an assortment of appetizers and beer for our group of 8. Nothing really stood out to us, but nothing was bad either. Meh.

Terrible service and mediocre food. Food was cold and bland. Server messed up 2 drinks, one dinner order and was MIA through most of the evening. We were visiting from out of town and wished we’d read the reviews before coming.

This was by far one of the worst dining experiences I've ever had. First, when we were seated we were given one menu for a party of four. Then after sitting for 5-10 minutes, a waitress finally appeared and took our drink orders. She mentioned at that time that the kitchen was a little slow that night. If we were smart, we would've gotten up and left at this point.  We ordered our meals and an appetizer, and thankfully the app came out quickly. After that the server did not come back to our table for at least 30 minutes. All around us parties were asking to speak to a manager and referencing having been there nearly 45 minutes without receiving any food. We were just about to get up and leave, after waiting nearly an hour for our food to come out, when the meals finally arrived. The waitress' exact words were "I hope everything came out well, it should've for how long it took."  Huge shock, the food was terrible. The chicken on 2 of our meals was cold, and tasted as if it had been sitting for 30+ minutes. Then, the waitress was too preoccupied with other angry parties to notice that our drinks were empty & that we were clearly not satisfied with our food, as 3/4 meals went almost entirely uneaten. We were in a rush to get to an event, so we did not have time to stay and argue with a manager who had already been to 4 different tables around us to try and calm down angry customers.  If it were possible to give this restaurant 0 stars, I certainly would.
The only item that I can'trecommended is the artichoke dip
Very slow service. Went on a non-busy evening and it took 45 minutes to get our food. Also, it arrived to us cold. Would not recommend this place to anyone!

Food was reasonably priced, large selection of drinks and beers to chose from. We will definitely go back, definitely bring others. Thank you guys for rescuing our day, we had a nice time!

Great service at the bar. Friendly people.

Delicious food, trendy area, friendly staff.

My boyfriend is allergic to dairy- the waitress brought him his entre with 1 of the 2 sides missing, and never actually noticed for the entire meal. The fries had parmesan cheese on them. love it the food is wonderful and is a wonderful place to work

Great Food, Great Service, Great Location in Downtown Louisville KY. Highly recommended.

Honestly, one of the best places I've eaten at. In town for 3 nights and came here twice, both meals were absolutely delicious. Veronica our server was fantastic and super friendly! Highly recommended.
This place is amazing! We were here for a long weekend and went here twice.  Veronica was our server and she was absolutely amazing 😊😊😊 highly recommend it 👍👍👍
Great service. Nice beer selection. Wings came out cold and not crispy, a bit mushy. Garlic fries were delicious. Sliders were also well done, just avoid the wings and nachos.
Good food good beer
Love the outdoors seating and fireplace. Good drinks too.
Great atmosphere! I love that you get to see into the kitchen. The entrees were mediocre at best, but the bread pudding for dessert, was phenomenal!!!

Great food and beer!!!
Very friendly staff.  Reasonable priced food  with great flavor!

The wings were good but nothing to rave about. Overall and okay experience.

We are staying at a hotel near Fourth Street Live for a couple days during the Christmas holiday break.  We thought we would give GB a try since they have many selections on their menu and that is a plus for my family's diverse tastes. Service - 3 stars.  Ambiance - 3.5 stars.  Food - 1 star.  My daughter and I split a 10 inch pepperoni pizza that was more like a 7 inch pizza + 3 inch crust.  The dough/crust dominated this pie and the sauce, cheese, and pepperoni were minimal.  Taste was just ok.  Do not order this!  My other daughter ordered the fish tacos and she said they were very bland.  My third daughter ordered the ciabatta turkey sandwich and there was a watery spread that dripped out with every bite.  She was not thrilled.  My wife ordered a chicken slider and side kale & quinoa salad and she was satisfied with both.  I had a Golden Export lager, which reminded me of Bud Light....nothing special about this beer at all.  Bottom line is that I left there with the strong feeling that I will never enter a GB restaurant again...one and done.

My suggestion if you decide to come here and your server is named steven, just leave.

this place is really nice. i asked the waiter in the front desk what do they sell here and she said we dont sell anything like chicken strips. haha. i guess she got foolish when i stayed and ordered a $30 meal ! but yeah the food was really good.
